# Presentation typography (required)

Text sizes follow **Hephaestus International. Version 3.pdf** (900pt slide width), not Material Design 3.

## How to size text

1. **Prefer semantic HTML** — `h1`–`h6`, `p`, `label`, `button`, `nav a`, etc. Base styles in `app/globals.css` apply presentation-proportional sizes automatically.
2. **Homepage story sections** — use `type.slideTitle`, `type.slideHeadline`, `type.slideLead`, `type.slideBody`, etc. from `@/lib/typography` for PDF-accurate roles.
3. **Or** use `components/ui/typography.tsx` (`SectionHeading` with `scale`, `Prose`, …).
4. **Or** apply a `.type-slide-*` / legacy `.type-*` utility class directly.

## PDF role reference (pt on 900pt slide)

| Token | PDF pt | Use for |
|-------|--------|---------|
| `slide-title` | 30 | Hero lines, section titles, transition copy |
| `slide-headline` | 24 | Secondary titles (positioning, pillars) |
| `slide-subhead` | 18 | Closing CTA questions, emphasis lines |
| `slide-lead` | 15 | Subtitles, card titles, emphasized body |
| `slide-body` | 12 | Default body, fact cards |
| `slide-number` | 14 | Pillar numbers |

Sizes are fluid (`clamp` + `vw`) so full-bleed sections scale like the deck. Tokens live in `app/globals.css`.
